- Exception is a runtime problem which occurs in the program and leads to program termination.
- Exception handling is a technique which handles the runtime problems and maintains the flow of program execution

- TRY, CATCH, FINALLY, THROW -> Keywords for exception handling

- Unchecked Exception: Exception which is thrown due to mistakes in our code. Extends the RuntimeException class
  Example: ArithmeticException, ArrayIndexOutOfBoundException, SecurityException, NullPointerException

- Checked exception: Exceptions checked at compile time. Extends Throwable class.